3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a novel centrality measure that aggregates different factors, which involves algorithmic techniques and data structures. 
4. cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) - The paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed centrality measure in large public networks, which is relevant to the sub-category of Cybersecurity. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a novel centrality measure that takes into account an individual's propensity to socialize, which involves AI techniques such as machine learning and natural language processing.
